Set up a Crucis verification pipeline for `{{ function_name }}`: {{ function_description }}

Steps:
1. Use crucis_init to scaffold the workspace if no objective.yaml exists
2. Edit objective.yaml:
   - Set name to '{{ function_name }}'
   - Set description to explain the behavior
   - Set signature to the function signature
   - Add examples (input/output pairs — holdout evals are auto-split)
   - Optionally add behaviors (natural-language descriptions)
   - Set target_files to where the implementation should go
3. Use crucis_validate to check the objective is valid
4. Use crucis_doctor to verify the environment is ready
5. Use the agent_tdd_workflow prompt to run the step-by-step workflow
6. Use crucis_summary to check results